Quote:  The thornfish, <i>Bovichtus variegatus</i>, is a rock-pool fish, up to ten inches long, of Stewart Island and the islands further south.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1981
Source:  Fisherman's Bible
Author:  WILSON
Vol / Page:  260
Edition:
Quote:  THORNFISH A distinguished-looking, but poor-eating, fish the scaleless Thornfish inhabits our inshore, rocky coasts in cooler waters from about the central North Island southwards.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1982
Source:  Collins Guide
Author:  AYLING
Vol / Page:  274
Edition:  1984
Quote:  <i>THORNFISH </i>(Horny, dragonet) <i>Bovichtus variegatus (Bovichthys variegatus) </i>... The thornfish is a small, cylindrical fish with scaleless body ... There is a distinctive strong spine directed upward and backward on each gill cover behind the eyes. ... Thornfish are common in tidepools ... from the Wellington area southwards ...
